summary: In this context, (3e)-3,7-dimethylocta-1,3,6-triene and methylheptenone are both mentioned as volatile organic compounds (VOCs) emitted by plants, particularly in response to MeJA treatment. However, there is no direct discussion of their specific relationship or interaction. They are part of a broader analysis of terpenes and other VOCs in treated versus control plants, indicating they may share a common pathway in plant metabolism but lack detailed interaction evidence.
